<h1 class="jazz-page-title">Icons</h1>

<p>
Icons are a compact visual means of quickly communicating a concept or idea.
</p>

{{ example("/design/icons/icons-example", "Icons Example", "code-panel-icons") }}

<h2>Best Practices</h2>

<ul>
    <li>Use icons to enhance pieces of your design, not to replace pieces of your design.</li>
    <li>Use icons that have a well-established meaning.</li>
    <li>Avoid attempting to represent abstract concepts with icons.</li>
    <li>Use icons consistently.  Icons should have a single meaning within the context that they are being used.  Icons should have a consistent meaning across all University sites.</li>
    <li>Keep icons simple.  A limited space is available to convey meaning.</li>
    <li>If a legend or training is necessary to explain the meaning of icons, then the icons should be made more clear or excluded from the design altogether.</li>
    <li>Icons should be paired with text wherever possible.</li>
    <li>Consider assistive devices.  Be sure to clearly indicate to assistive devices that an icon is decorative.</li>
    <li>Provide additional metadata to assistive devices when an icon is not accompanied by a textual label.</li>
    <li>Icons are most useful as part of another component (Button, Link, Tab, Menu, etc…).</li>
</ul>

